Two domestic staff, a gateman and housekeeper, were on Wednesday charged at a Kubwa Magistrates ‘ Court in Abuja for allegedly stealing valuables worth N13 million belonging to their employer. The defendants, Thomas Loson, who resides at Tungan Wakili Dei-Dei, Abuja, and Amina Augustine of Third Avenue, Gwarimpa Estate, also in Abuja, are facing two counts of alleged joint act and stealing. However, the two domestic staff pleaded not guilty to the charges. Police Prosecutor, ASP Peter Ejike, told the court that the defendants on Nov. 3, conspired and stole a box of jewellery, Samsung Galaxy phone and other valuable items valued at N13 million, property of Mrs Victoria Edeh. According to Ejike, the complainant, Mrs Victoria Edeh, who resides at No. 24, Third Avenue, Gwarimpa Estate, Abuja, reported the theft at the Police Area Command, Life Camp, Abuja. He said the offences contravened the provisions of Sections 79 and 289 of the Penal Code. The Magistrate, Mrs Muinat Oyekan admitted the defendants to bail in the sum of N500,000 each with one reasonable surety each in like sum. Muinat ordered that the sureties must reside within the court’s jurisdiction and adjourned the case until Dec. 4 for continuation of hearing. (NAN) Housekeeper, driver, arraigned for allegedly stealing Odegbami’s wife’s N150m jewellery Police arraign trader over theft of N191,500 electronics Police arraign applicant for allegedly stealing 53 cartons of tiles , 2 Italian doors Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.